:: context id=ctx:advanced-theory priority=low depth=detailed collapse=true
@summary: "CPython internals: memory model, GIL, bytecode compilation."
@max_tokens: 3000

Python uses reference counting with a generational garbage collector.
The GIL (Global Interpreter Lock) ensures thread safety for CPython
but limits true parallelism for CPU-bound tasks.
